22 WHEREAS, Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Incorporated was founded January 16,
23 1920, at Howard University in Washington, D.C., during a time of often
24 violent racial turmoil in the nation but also the Harlem Renaissance, one of
25 the first important domestic movements of Black artists and writers in the
26 United States; and
27
28 WHEREAS, Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Incorporated serves and advocates for
29 social, health, and economic justice both domestically and globally and
30 remains poised for perpetual service to mankind into its second century of
31 existence and beyond; and
32
33 WHEREAS, the members of Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Incorporated uphold the
34 sorority's ideals of Scholarship, Service, Sisterhood, and Finer Womanhood;
35 and
